tax information
because it's currently available
tax data.

14:06.946 --> 14:11.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the past, we asked students
to transfer
the date that really wasn't
available until

14:12.085 --> 14:13.753 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tax filing deadlines.

14:13.853 --> 14:16.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But now we're going back another
year to make
it more available and easier for
students

14:16.823 --> 14:20.393 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to populate the forms with that
income information
that is sometimes hard to find.

14:20.493 --> 14:23.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now, there is
also that
gap between when you found out
if a school

14:23.896 --> 14:28.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wanted you or not and then
another couple
of weeks or months to figure out
what kind

14:28.534 --> 14:30.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of financial aid you were going
to get from
them.

14:30.336 --> 14:32.105 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KIM COOK: Exactly.

14:32.205 --> 14:36.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, because of the filing times
that used
to be in January, financial aid
offices were

14:36.509 --> 14:40.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
under the gun to get award
applications out
to students, so that they could
make informed

14:40.413 --> 14:44.717 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
decisions about what kind of aid
was available
at each particular school, and
where they

14:44.817 --> 14:46.686 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
